Replaced four internal ``assert`` statements in the parsing pipeline with explicit :class:`TypeError`/:class:`ValueError` checks. Python's ``-O`` flag strips all ``assert`` statements, which silently disabled validation in :class:`~icalendar.parser.content_line.Contentline` (embedded newlines) and in ``_escape_char``, ``_unescape_char``, and ``_foldline`` (type checks and embedded newlines). Under ``-O``, this allowed invalid content lines to be produced instead of raising an error. These checks are now unconditional regardless of the ``-O`` flag.
